🧭 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Create Excel sheets for Fact_Sales, Dim_Product, Dim_Customer, Dim_Date, and Dim_Geography with the given structure.
2.	Open Microsoft Power BI Desktop.
3.	Click Home → Get Data → Excel and select the file.
4.	Load all five tables into Power BI.
5.	Go to Model View (Diagram icon on the left panel).
6.	Identify the Fact_Sales table as the central fact table.
7.	Drag ProductKey from Dim_Product to Fact_Sales to create a relationship.
8.	Drag CustomerKey from Dim_Customer to Fact_Sales to create a relationship.
9.	Drag DateKey from Dim_Date to Fact_Sales to create a relationship.
10.	(Optional) Link Dim_Geography to Dim_Customer using GeoKey, if present.
11.	Ensure all relationships are One-to-Many from Dimension to Fact table.
12.	Verify the final model forms a Star Schema with Fact_Sales at the center and dimension tables around it.

